node.text:
Go behind the design with Nike Materials Designer Francesca Capone-Jones (@franny_capone) and environmental journalist Sophia Li (@sophfei) as they break down the details discussing how two iconic Nike styles were reimagined with sustainability in mind.

Skip Around:
Catch up on Nike's Move to Zero initiative with Sophia Li and meet Nike Materials Designer, Francesca Capone-Jones (3:55), as she breaks down the innovation behind the all new Air Force 1 Crater and Waffle Racer Crater (10:50). Plus, get a crash course from a pro on the principles of sustainable design (30:45) before hearing Francesca answer questions from the audience (38:45). 

Shop AF1 Crater and Waffle Crater: 
http://smarturl.it/craterbts

node.title: Behind the Design: AF1 Crater and Waffle Crater

Growing up in South Africa, @karabo_poppy was obsessed with art, but couldn’t find herself or her experiences reflected in it.
⠀
Karabo uses unconventional canvases like basketball courts and city streets—things people interact with in their everyday life. That’s why she is so drawn to the Air Force 1 for her artwork.
⠀
This season, Karabo’s artwork graces the Air Force 1 through Nike By You. #af1 #allfor1 #nikebyyou

“My culture is what got me into style -- looking at my uncles, my granddad and the older people in my life, those are the style cues that I took from. Cynthia likes to wear these Mexican embroidered shirts, like her grandmother.” - @travisgumbs ✨

@cynthiaxcervantes and @travisgumbs are partners in life and creativity.🤝 Founders of creative studio Maroon World, they capture the vibrancy of Black, Latinx and Indigenous communities.💫 The couple, who recently moved to Mexico City from New York with their son, Tenoch, aim to challenge tired notions of identity. “Everything that we do is rooted in intention,” says Cynthia. Read our interview with the pair through our 🔗 in bio. 

📝: @devinemarieblacksher 
📸: @dorianuliseslopezmacias 
Studio partner: @see.me.creative

Meet Henny Jones @hennykicksit, an LA Icon with a magnetic passion for sneakers like nobody you’ve seen before.✨

Driven by an unshakeable confidence and love for sneaker culture, Henny moved out to LA with her 12-year-old son in hopes of finding her dream job— and she did just that. She now works at @sneakersnstuff.la, working to break barriers, change the game, and create an inclusive community for women collectors just like her.🙌

Check out @nikelosangeles for more LA Icons.👀

“Security is the key to everything. Wear what feels comfortable in your size and wear it safely and with love.” - @murderette_ 🔑

Ro knows a thing or two about style. Running her own private hair styling studio in Mexico City, she specializes in bold colors and finding cuts that fit each client’s personality. 💇 Self expression through her hair, her style and her sneakers is key for Ro. She stepped in front of the camera and showed us how she rocks the Waffle One in her salon, at her crib and when she’s out on the town. 👟

#NikeWaffleOne is available now through our IG store.

Los Angeles, home of fashion-forward streetwear, sport-led style, and most importantly, women shaping a new world in sneaker culture - in our eyes, home of Icons. 

Introducing our first LA Icon, Beth Birkett. She’s a creative director, community leader, and visionary.✨

As the co-owner of @unionlosangeles and founder of @bephiesbeautysupply, she elevates up-and-coming artists and entrepreneurs daily. She works to change the gatekeepers of streetwear and to pass the baton to other Black and Brown creatives, just as it was passed to her. She doesn’t believe her legacy lies within what she personally creates, but with the creative community she cultivates.👏

Check out @nikelosangeles for more LA Icons.👀

Brooklyn-based stylist, creative director and self-described ‘sockfluencer’ Gia Seo keeps a keen eye on the details when it comes to her style.🧦 Finding freedom in exploring everything from patterns and textures to backdrops and colors, Gia put herself in front of the lens to show us how the Waffle One complements her style.🌀

#NikeWaffleOne is available now through our IG store.

 Summer isn’t summer without the sun. 😎  But the sun can be very hot and sunburns hurt!🔥 Fear not. All you need to do is make friends with that big, bright and impressive star in our sky, and it’s smooth sailing from there. Follow these pro-Summering tips to maximize your 🍦 enjoyment.
